##  Installation
### Prerequisites
- [Clarinet](https://github.com/hirosystems/clarinet) for development and testing
- [Stacks CLI](https://docs.stacks.co/docs/stacks-cli) for deployment
- Node.js and npm for testing

### Setup
```bash
# Clone the repository
git clone https://github.com/your-org/stacks-innovation-lab.git
cd stacks-innovation-lab

# Install dependencies
npm install

# Run tests
clarinet test

# Check contract
clarinet check
```
##  Contract Architecture
### Data Structures

#### Core Maps
- **`innovation-challenges`**: Stores challenge metadata, deadlines, and status
- **`solution-submissions`**: Stores participant solutions and metadata
- **`challenge-participation-registry`**: Tracks participant submissions per challenge
- **`authorized-challenge-evaluators`**: Manages evaluator permissions
- **`detailed-submission-evaluations`**: Stores evaluation scores and feedback
- **`participant-reward-allocations`**: Tracks reward distribution

#### Security Maps
- **`validated-string-inputs`**: Safe storage for validated string inputs
- **`validated-hash-inputs`**: Safe storage for validated hash inputs

### Challenge Lifecycle

```
┌─────────────────┐    ┌─────────────────┐    ┌─────────────────┐
│   SUBMISSION    │    │   EVALUATION    │    │   FINALIZED     │
│     PERIOD      │───▶│     PERIOD      │───▶│     STATE       │
│  (Phase 1)      │    │   (Phase 2)     │    │   (Phase 3)     │
└─────────────────┘    └─────────────────┘    └─────────────────┘
```

